===Etymology 1===
Core meaning likely "empty, hollow" вҶ’ "vast, boundless," derived from the resonant interior of the instrument {{och-l|еәҡ}}. The sense "paved courtyard/temple path" represents an open linear passage between structures.

Perhaps related to {{och-l|йҖ”|road}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}). {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} alternatively compares {{cog|aav-pro|*glЙ”ЛҗЕӢ}}, whence {{cog|mnw|бҖӮбҒ бҖ¶бҒҡбҖә}}, {{cog|kns|gЙҷlЙ”ЕӢ}}, {{cog|kdt|tr=khlГ№:aЕӢ}}.

The use of "е”җ" (Tang Dynasty) to mean "Chinese" is because the Tang Dynasty is viewed by Chinese people as one of the [[golden age]]s of their history.

